━━ INPUT FORMAT ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Each segment has:
  • "master_text"  — Chinese ASR transcript (what was SPOKEN; phonetically reliable)
  • "context_text" — Chinese OCR text (what is DISPLAYED; may be censored or garbled)
  • "start" / "end" — exact timestamps to preserve in output

━━ YOUR TASK ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
1.  **Censored-word restoration** (highest priority)
    Short dramas frequently censor aggressive dialogue on screen.  When
    "context_text" shows a censored or masked form and "master_text" gives
    you the phonetic ground truth, restore the authentic word.

    Common patterns (OCR → authentic):
      "弄S你" / "弄*你" / "弄○你"  →  "弄死你"    (ASR: "nòng sǐ nǐ")
      "S人"  / "S了他"             →  "死人" / "死了他"
      "废S"  / "废★"               →  "废物"
      "去S"  / "去★"               →  "去死"
      "狅"   / "狂*"               →  "狂"  (confirm with ASR)
      "SB"   / "S.B."              →  contextually infer; retain if unclear
      Any symbol (★☆✖●▲♦) replacing a character  →  infer from ASR phonetics

    Decision rule:
      • ASR "master_text" gives the phonetic reality — trust it over OCR.
      • If ASR is also unclear, use the short-drama confrontation context
        (争吵、威胁、傲娇 are dominant tones) to infer the most natural word.
      • If genuinely ambiguous, output the ASR text verbatim without inventing.

2.  **Character name unification**
    Correct every name variant to the canonical form from the Character
    Reference above.  Examples: "霍健华" / "霍剑华" / "货建华"  →  the
    canonical form listed in meta_json.

3.  **OCR/ASR conflict resolution**
    When "context_text" (OCR) and "master_text" (ASR) differ in phrasing:
      • If the difference is clearly a display censorship → rule 1 above.
      • If OCR looks like an ASR homophone error → trust OCR display.
      • If both are unintelligible → output ASR verbatim.

4.  **Light copyediting only** — do NOT rewrite dialogue, do NOT add
    punctuation the source does not have.  Preserve every segment's
    start/end timestamp exactly.
    You MAY merge consecutive segments when at least one has duration ≤ 0.3 s:
    concatenate the Chinese text (no space) and use the first start / last end
    timestamp.  Do NOT split segments.

━━ OUTPUT FORMAT ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
